The Director shall, within thirty days of receipt of the application for a licence made under subsection (2)•
* issue the licence to the applicant if the applicant meets the requirements of this Act; or
* reject the application if it does not meet the requirements of this Act, and inform the applicant of the reasons for the rejection.
* forest produce conveyance permit, to allow the holder to convey forest produce;
* forest produce merchantâ¢s permit, to allow the holder to trade in forest produce;
* forest produce export permit, to allow the holder to export forest produce;
* forest produce import permit, to allow the holder to import forest produce;
* domestic user permit, to allow the holder to harvest or use forest produce for domestic purposes;
* cord-wood permit, to allow the holder to harvest or use wood for firework or charcoal production;
* forest fire permit, to allow the holder to set a forest fire for purposes of forest management; and
* tree-felling permit, to allow the holder to fell a tree or trees.
* issue the permit to the applicant if the applicant meets the requirements of this Act; or
* reject the application made if it does not meet the requirements of this Act, and inform the applicant of the reasons for the rejection.
* reject the application made if it does not meet the requirements of this Act, and inform the applicant of the reasons for the rejection.
 Permits

The Minister may, on the recommendation of the Director, prescribe the terms and conditions for licences and permits which shall specify•
* the circumstances under which the licences or permits may be suspended, cancelled or renewed;
* the fees and penalties for non payment of fees;
* the conditions for the felling, cutting, taking, removal, conversion, processing, transport or sale of forest produce;
* the activities for prevention and fighting of fires;
* the form of records and returns to be submitted by persons engaged in the cutting, taking, removal, conversion, processing, transportation, sale or use of forest produce;
* the payment of compensation for damage to trees, growing crops,roads, tracks, paths, bridges, waterways and other improvements in forest areas;
* the making good of any damage to land in forest areas;
* the conduct of any silvicultural activities;
* the quantity of forest produce to be harvested;
* the requirements for afforestation and reforestation; and
* any other matter which the Director may recommend for purposes of this Act.
* any works or improvement in the forest area effected by the licensee or permit holder;
* any loss suffered by the licensee or permit holder as a result of the suspension or cancellation of the licence or permit;

any damage to, or loss of, any forest produce before its removal from the licence or permit area or coupe.
* A licence  or permit shall not be granted in an area which is the subject of another licence or permit issued under this Act.
* Unless a contrary intention is expressly stated on a licence or permit, rights under the  licence or permit  shall not extend toâ¢
	* any land dedicated as a place of burial;
<\li2>
	* any land within thirty metres of the centre line of any public road;
	* any land within thirty metres of the boundary of any rail reserve;
	* any land within fifty metres of a bank or edge of any river;
	* any land within thirty metres of a power line; or
	* grazing land.

(1) An authorised officer may, for the  purposes of this Act•
* take or cause to be taken from any forest produce, major forest produce or protected flora, any sample or specimen;
* take or cause to be taken from any land, building, premises or conveyance, any sample or specimen; and
* apply such other tests as the authorised officer considers necessary.
* has committed an offence under this Act;
* is about to commit an offence under this Act and there is no other way to prevent the commission of the offence; or

An authorised officer who receives a payment under this section and•
* fails to issue a receipt to the person making the payment as required under subsection (5);
* fails to account for any payment made under this section; or
* in any manner, misuses or puts to personal use any payment made under this section;
* order the cancellation of the licence  or permit held by that person;
* assess the amount of compensation for the loss or damage caused by that person in the commission of the offence and cause the compensation to be recovered from that person as if it were a debt due and payable to the Government;

Without prejudice to the generality of subsection (1), regulations made under that subsection may provide for•
* the survey and demarcation of National Forests and Local Forests;
* the protection and management of flora in forest areas and open areas;
* the development and implementation of forest management plans by the Department and local  communities, joint forest management committees, Chiefs and other stakeholders;
* the form of participation of local communities and Chiefs which ensures equitable gender participation;
* the registers for forest management plans, licences and permits;
* the establishment of commercial plantations and woodlots;
* the marking of timber from private forests and the conveyance fees to be paid for the timber;
* the utilisation, conservation and planting of trees on State Land, customary areas and open areas;
* the prohibition and regulation of the cutting and taking of forest produce;
* the management of Local Forests by local communities, Chiefs, local authorities and  other stakeholders;
* the implementation of  international agreements to which Zambia is a State Party;
* the sharing of forest revenue with local communities;
* the fees to be paid for licences and permits issued under this Act;
* carbon stock management;
* the regulation of beekeeping; and
* the administration and management of the Fund.
* the administration and management of the Fund.
